[package]
name = "git"
version = "0.1.0"
description = "git — global gitconfig"

[[link]]
source = ".gitconfig"
target = ".gitconfig"

---

# git

One file. The repo `.gitconfig` is a strict superset of the
typical fresh-install on-disk version (adds the `[github]`
section). `~/.config/git/ignore` is intentionally NOT in
this package — it carries a local-only `**/.claude/settings.local.json`
pattern that doesn't belong in a shared dotfile repo.
